We have a system like that in the Netherlands. Jobs are funded (partly) by the government (for people who have low chance of getting a job) so that they build experience so they can enter the market again after a few years. This doesn't work well though, because the experience they get is not really useful for the market. They receive a little money than wellfare, but are under minimum wage.<br>
