Okay, but to start a business there HAS to be a market for them to sell their product to. There has to be money to fund those businesses, it takes time to stretch the market to be able to create a more healthy economic environment. There is a limit to how many new businesses the market can support.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The more new businesses you have, the more new spending you have, which creates need for even more businesses.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
