True, but this is a slow process, it isn't like an economy in recession can instantly support businesses for, say, the people who got unemployed in the last year. I am not saying it is impossible for anyone to start a new business at any time. But the climb out of a recession is as slow for any system, capitalism or socialism.<br>
<br>
Granted, in the USA there is an environment that supports this process much more than here in Europe, but that is mostly because of the ease to get credit in the USA. It has little to do with socialism vs. capitalism.<br>
